2"},"displayName":"Sebastien Dionne","active":true},"created":"2013-03-08T14:22:10.305+0000","updated":"2013-03-08T14:22:10.305+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12635867/comment/13597169","id":"13597169","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=survivant","name":"survivant","emailAddress":"survivant00 at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Sebastien Dionne","active":true},"body":"if I understand, the PostingsHighlighter, could return a portion of the text scan ?  In my call, I ask for 50 Passages Max, he did stop after 4 passages, before the text [0] wasn't found anymore.  That's fine here.  but for me the point of a Highlighter, is to Highlighter all the match (until the max occurences is found , here 50).  and return the text scanned with its highlights.\r\n\r\nI see that Highlighter like a \"FIND ALL\" that will highlights the all the occurences of the word.  \r\n\r\nby reading the javadoc, it's what I though this Highlighter was suppose to do.  If not, I'll just have to create a new one that will do that.\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=survivant","name":"survivant","emailAddress":"survivant00 at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Sebastien Dionne","active":true},"created":"2013-